The United States and Japan have agreed to work together to address global challenges. They have highlighted several areas of cooperation, including humanitarian assistance and disaster relief, development assistance, global health, empowerment of women, and contributions to global security. The two countries are committed to providing support and assistance to countries affected by natural disasters, particularly in Southeast Asia. They will also coordinate their efforts in providing development assistance, with a focus on Southeast Asia, the Pacific region, and Africa. In terms of global health, Japan has pledged $800 million to the Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Malaria, and Tuberculosis, which will be matched by the United States. Both countries are committed to achieving the Millennium Development Goals and empowering women. They also support Middle East peace efforts and are committed to providing humanitarian assistance in Syria. Lastly, Japan and the United States will work together to promote maritime safety and security.